                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d407">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">711.93/121: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Japan</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">MacVeagh</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Tokyo</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1927-01-29T16:00:00+09:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">January 29, 1927—4 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/>[Received January 29—9:25 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>11. Secretary’s statement on Chinese policy well received here by Japanese press
                    which feels that in general it coincides with Japanese Government’s policy.
                    Although I have not discussed statement with Foreign Office, I understand from
                    colleague who has talked with Vice Minister that they are pleased with stand we
                    have taken.</p>
                <p>Full text not being available here I have asked Peking to forward copy.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">MacVeagh</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
